description: Regenerate managed SamQL full source before committing product changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Managed full-source commit order

For every SamQL product or release commit that changes managed source:

1. Update the release identity when the release process requires it.
2. Regenerate and verify the canonical full-source bundle under `samql_txt/`
   from the current intended source tree, using the project release tooling.
3. Commit all intended changes, including the updated
   `samql_txt/samql_full_source_all_tests_ui_<build>.txt`, in the same commit.

Do not commit managed-source changes first and defer the `samql_txt/` refresh
to a later commit. Leave generated release packaging artifacts untracked unless
they are explicitly intended product files.
